Store No. 26363

STATE OF FLORIDA
COUNTY OF ORANGE

THIRD AMENDMENT
TO LEASE AGREEMENT

THIS THIRD AMENDMENT TO LEASE AGREEMENT ("Amendment") is executed as of the 24th day of August, 2020 (the "Effective Date") by and between LF2 UNIVERSITY, LP, a Florida limited partnership ("Landlord"), and FAMILY DOLLAR STORES OF FLORIDA, LLC, a Virginia limited liability company ("Tenant").

WITNESSETH:

WHEREAS, Landlord and Tenant are parties to that certain Lease Agreement dated April 5, 2004, as amended by that certain (i) First Amendment to Lease dated January 26, 2010, and (ii) Second Amendment to Lease Agreement dated July 26, 2019, and those certain Letter Agreements dated June 18, 2004 and April 7, 2006 (collectively, the "Lease") with respect to certain premises situated in Landlord's shopping center known as University Plaza (formerly known as K-Mart Plaza) located on North Goldenrod Road, in the City of Winter Park, County of Orange, State of Florida, as more specifically described in the Lease (the "demised premises") and identified by Tenant as Store No. 26363; and

WHEREAS, the current term of the Lease, being the second extended term, expires June 30, 2020; and

WHEREAS, Landlord and Tenant have reached an agreement to further modify and extend the term of the Lease as set forth herein.

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing, and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt of which is hereby acknowledged, and the mutual covenants hereinafter contained, Landlord and Tenant agree that:

1. EXTENDED TERMS AND RENT. The current term of the Lease, being second extended term, is scheduled to expire on June 30, 2020. Landlord and Tenant agree that the Lease is extended through the third extended term (July 1, 2020 through June 30, 2025). All of the terms, covenants and conditions of the Lease will apply to the third extended term, except that fixed rent for the third extended term will be ELEVEN THOUSAND ONE HUNDRED THIRTY-EIGHT AND 50/100 DOLLARS ($11,138.50) per month ($133,656.60/annum) plus applicable sales tax on rent assessed by the State of Florida and the county, if applicable.

The Lease provides for one (1) remaining extended term of five (5) years (the fourth extended term). All of the terms, covenants and conditions of the Lease will apply to the fourth extended term, except that fixed rent shall be as set forth below, plus applicable sales tax on rent assessed by the State of Florida and the county, if applicable:

For all purposes under the Lease, as amended by this Amendment, the phrases "the term of this lease" and "lease term" will mean the current term, as extended, and any extended term that comes into effect pursuant to the Lease as amended.

2. USE OF PREMISES. Paragraph 3 of the Lease is hereby amended by adding the following:

"If Tenant elects, in its sole discretion, to sell alcoholic beverages from the demised premises for off-premises consumption, Landlord will at no expense to Landlord, and promptly following Tenant's request, reasonably cooperate with Tenant to obtain any required governmental licenses, permits and approvals, including signing, any required license, permit and other applications in order to evidence Landlord's consent to such application and sale."

3. TAXES. Effective July 1, 2020, Paragraph 13 of the Lease is hereby deleted and replaced with the following:

"13. TAXES. Landlord will pay all taxes, assessments and other charges which may be levied, assessed or charged against the shopping center including the demised premises.

Tenant will pay all operating license fees for the conduct of its business, and ad valorem taxes levied upon its trade fixtures, inventory and other personal property. Tenant will reimburse Landlord for Tenant's proportionate shares of the real estate taxes (including both ad valorem and non-ad valorem assessments) on the shopping center plus applicable sales tax on rent assessed by the State of Florida and the county, if applicable.

In addition, Tenant will reimburse Landlord for Tenant's proportionate share (as defined herein) of all reasonable expenses, including, without limitation, attorneys' fees and disbursements, experts, and other witnesses fees incurred in contesting the validity or amount of any taxes or in obtaining a refund of taxes (collectively "Landlord's Tax Contest Costs"), provided, however, Tenant will not be obligated to pay any portion of Landlord's Tax Contest Costs in excess of the total tax savings over a two year period resulting from Landlord's contest. Tenant's proportionate share will be equal to a fraction, the numerator of which will be the number of square feet of floor area in the demised premises, and the denominator of which will be the total number of square feet of floor area in all buildings in the shopping center, including the demised premises, but excluding the area of any buildings demised pursuant to land leases (provided such land and buildings are on separately assessed tax parcels). Landlord's good faith estimate of Tenant's reimbursement for the year 2020 is $19,392.00. The amount of real estate taxes to be reimbursed by Tenant will be reduced on a per diem basis for partial lease years.

When this Amendment is signed by Landlord or Tenant, Landlord or Tenant may deliver copies of this Amendment to he other party via electronic delivery, including, without limitation, e-mail or fax. Delivery of a party's signed counterpart of this Amendment via electronic delivery will be as valid and binding upon the parties as are original ink signatures.

5. LANDLORD AND TENANT WARRANTIES. Landlord represents and warrants that Landlord has full right and lawful authority to enter into this Amendment for the present term and all extensions. In addition, Landlord's representations, covenants and warranties of title and authority set forth in the Lease are hereby renewed and restated by Landlord. Landlord also represents and warrants that no consent or approval of any mortgagee of the demised premises or any other entity is required.

Tenant represents and warrants that Tenant has full right and lawful authority to enter into this Amendment.

It is mutually understood and agreed that the Lease will remain in full force and effect except as specifically modified and amended by this Amendment. All covenants, terms, obligations and conditions of the Lease, which are not modified or amended, are hereby ratified and confirmed.
